ref-12-3-2                    Xerox Quintus Prolog Reference Manual                      Section 12-3-2: Exhaustive TracingYou can start creeping, or single-stepping, by typing a goal while trace modeis in force, or by selecting the creep option when the debugger prompts you forinput.When creeping, the debugger displays a message whenever it goes through anyport of any procedure box.  By default, it stops after displaying this messageand prompts you for input.  You have a number of options at this point,including those of creeping again or of leaping to the next spypoint.